WEBVTT

01:43.135 --> 01:45.205
[birds chirping]

02:17.102 --> 02:18.371
Hey.

02:19.138 --> 02:20.173
We're done.

02:20.306 --> 02:22.142
All right.

02:23.175 --> 02:24.777
[sighs]

02:44.063 --> 02:45.765
There you go. Thanks.

02:47.900 --> 02:49.269
Thanks.

02:52.338 --> 02:53.773
Thanks.

03:05.351 --> 03:07.587
[beeping]

03:08.487 --> 03:11.291
[line ringing] [sighs]

03:12.925 --> 03:15.828
[woman] Allô? [operator] You have
a collect call from...

03:16.062 --> 03:17.630
Daniel Léger.

03:17.763 --> 03:19.799
[operator] Would you like to
accept charges?

03:19.932 --> 03:21.600
[woman] Yes.

03:21.734 --> 03:23.703
[in French]

04:04.977 --> 04:06.379
Uh...

04:20.426 --> 04:22.929
Allô? [line clicks, dial tone]

04:26.099 --> 04:27.834
$7.50. [in English] Yeah.

04:30.402 --> 04:32.105
Add, uh, one of these,
okay? Yeah.

04:32.238 --> 04:35.375
Let me just go
grab my wallet.
I'll be right back.

04:48.120 --> 04:49.622
[engine starting]

04:50.956 --> 04:52.458
Hey!

04:55.795 --> 04:59.164
At any given time,
about how many children
do you have in your care

04:59.298 --> 05:00.933
at the institution,
Mr. Woodbridge?

05:01.067 --> 05:03.803
Despite massive cuts
in government grants,

05:03.936 --> 05:06.705
we've managed to keep caring
for more than 20 kids,

05:06.839 --> 05:08.574
which is why we
created the foundation--

05:08.707 --> 05:10.142
Yes, but before we get to that,

05:10.276 --> 05:11.543
I'd like you to outline
your methods

05:11.677 --> 05:13.212
for dealing with
difficult children,

05:13.346 --> 05:14.681
if you don't mind.

05:14.814 --> 05:15.915
Certainly, uh,

05:16.048 --> 05:19.518
but, if I may finish,
the foundation--

05:19.651 --> 05:22.521
Now, I'm speaking specifically
about the recent suicides

05:22.654 --> 05:24.790
of two young boys,
ages 11 and 12,

05:24.924 --> 05:27.593
that were in your care
at the institution.

05:29.561 --> 05:31.830
Norm! No, no. Not now.

05:31.964 --> 05:33.132
[device vibrating]

05:33.265 --> 05:34.466
What was that?

05:34.599 --> 05:36.568
[vibrating continues]

05:37.035 --> 05:40.039
Somebody's trying to get
ahold of you, Mr. Malarek.

05:40.406 --> 05:42.608
And I think it's time
for me to leave too.

05:43.109 --> 05:45.777
Oh, shit. We have testimonies on tape
if you'd like to hear them

05:45.911 --> 05:47.813
and refresh your memory,
you piece of shit.

05:47.947 --> 05:50.782
[Norm]
Mr. Woodbridge, I'm so sorry
about the interruption.

05:50.916 --> 05:54.386
I-I-- We have a few
more questions. Mr.--

05:55.020 --> 05:57.089
Why in the hell did you leave
your pager on, man?

05:57.222 --> 05:59.458
Ah, it doesn't matter.
We got that son of a bitch.

05:59.592 --> 06:01.494
I know, but if it went off
20 seconds earlier,

06:01.627 --> 06:04.296
we would've had nothing. Yeah, but did you see
the look on his face?

06:04.430 --> 06:06.032
I did. Victor, security left
a message.

06:06.165 --> 06:09.268
Some guys from the Da Silva
gang are looking for you.

06:09.402 --> 06:11.904
They're here? Yeah. Front reception.

06:12.405 --> 06:13.740
Ah...

06:14.507 --> 06:15.875
[sighs]

06:18.377 --> 06:20.947
Victor, what
is this about? What?

06:21.447 --> 06:23.483
Do you want me
to call the police? Shit.

06:25.584 --> 06:26.986
Do you want me
to call the police?

06:27.119 --> 06:28.187
What? The police.

06:28.321 --> 06:30.089
No! No, no, no, no.
No police.

06:32.257 --> 06:33.493
Get your camera.

06:37.463 --> 06:39.264
[man 1] He's here!
Come on, let's go!

06:39.731 --> 06:42.068
[man 2] Malarek! Malarek!

06:43.870 --> 06:45.104
Shit.

06:47.339 --> 06:49.908
Where are you going?
Malarek, stop!

06:50.709 --> 06:52.578
Get in the car! [Norm] Let's go.

06:52.711 --> 06:54.814
Get these fuckers!
Get them!

06:56.516 --> 06:58.885
Are you filming?
Rolling? Okay, let's go.

07:04.023 --> 07:06.492
[tires squealing]

07:07.794 --> 07:08.927
Fuck.

07:09.428 --> 07:11.464
[tires screeching]

07:25.944 --> 07:26.979
Oh, shit.

07:30.616 --> 07:32.218
Oh, shit.

07:41.661 --> 07:43.129
Aw, fuck me.

07:44.496 --> 07:46.599
[bell ringing]

07:56.409 --> 07:59.045
[tires squealing]

08:10.289 --> 08:13.125
You run from us to a hospital?
Expect to get hurt, Malarek?

08:13.258 --> 08:15.928
You think I'm running away
from you, you piece of shit?

08:16.461 --> 08:17.696
Huh?

08:18.597 --> 08:20.532
Write another article
about Da Silva,

08:20.666 --> 08:22.701
we'll make sure
you end up in here.

08:22.834 --> 08:24.370
Let's get out of here.

08:24.503 --> 08:26.906
You tell Da Silva
he can kiss my ass.

08:30.242 --> 08:31.711
[elevator bell dings]

08:32.044 --> 08:33.278
Oh!

08:33.646 --> 08:35.480
Hi. I'm looking
for Anna Malarek's room.

08:35.614 --> 08:37.049
Victor! Anna Mala--

08:37.182 --> 08:38.417
Oh, God. Denise.

08:38.550 --> 08:40.118
We paged you over
and over.

08:40.252 --> 08:42.020
I was in an interview. I hope it was worth it.

08:42.154 --> 08:44.257
It cost you a moment
you'll never get back.

08:44.991 --> 08:47.793
She's done already? Some things don't work
around your schedule.

08:47.927 --> 08:50.196
How is she? She's fine.

08:52.698 --> 08:54.534
[sighs]

09:04.910 --> 09:07.146
[Victor whispering]
Hey. Hey.

09:07.513 --> 09:09.148
I'm so sorry.

09:09.281 --> 09:10.416
It's okay.

09:10.549 --> 09:12.118
No, it's not.

09:12.818 --> 09:14.620
I missed everything.

09:15.454 --> 09:17.223
She moves fast.

09:17.790 --> 09:19.625
Like her dad.

09:23.529 --> 09:25.064
There you go.

09:27.866 --> 09:30.036
Yeah, that's your dad.

09:30.469 --> 09:31.737
Oh.

09:32.437 --> 09:33.906
Hi.

09:37.944 --> 09:39.312
Yeah.

09:43.782 --> 09:45.717
Hey! Hey, hey, hey.

09:46.318 --> 09:48.321
Stay with me. Yeah.

09:50.523 --> 09:51.958
Good.

09:53.525 --> 09:56.394
Wow. Well done.

09:56.528 --> 09:58.097
Thanks.

10:10.743 --> 10:13.079
[siren wailing in distance]

10:18.451 --> 10:21.153
[chattering]

10:41.907 --> 10:43.375
Dubé got the job?

10:43.943 --> 10:45.645
Yeah, they just
announced it.

10:46.344 --> 10:47.713
I figured.

10:48.881 --> 10:50.850
Probably found out
Friday night,

10:50.983 --> 10:52.851
kept his mouth shut.

10:52.985 --> 10:54.987
I don't know what the hell
they were thinking.

10:55.120 --> 10:56.188
[chuckles]

10:56.322 --> 10:57.757
Lowest pay grade.

11:00.526 --> 11:01.827
What?

11:02.561 --> 11:03.963
I'm fine.

11:06.965 --> 11:08.968
I knew I wasn't gonna get it.

11:46.371 --> 11:48.107
[rattles door handle]

11:57.282 --> 11:58.617
Can I help you?

11:59.351 --> 12:01.921
Uh, I'm the guy
who rented this place.

12:02.054 --> 12:03.989
You must have
the wrong address.

12:04.824 --> 12:06.158
Um...

12:06.458 --> 12:07.492
Where's Michael?

12:07.793 --> 12:09.395
You know Michael?

12:11.497 --> 12:13.565
[Victor] What do you mean,
I don't deliver?

12:14.499 --> 12:18.270
Well, uh, we haven't had
anything from you
in two months.

12:18.404 --> 12:19.971
I just gave you
the Da Silva story.

12:20.105 --> 12:21.540
That was
a follow-up piece.

12:22.107 --> 12:23.475
You want
shocking stories?

12:23.608 --> 12:24.743
They take
serious research.

12:24.876 --> 12:27.579
Long-term investigations
take time.

12:27.712 --> 12:29.147
Then perhaps
you should spend

12:29.280 --> 12:30.749
a little less time
on your TV show

12:30.883 --> 12:32.351
and a little more time
here with us.

12:32.485 --> 12:34.553
The TV thing's part-time.
You know that.

12:34.687 --> 12:38.324
Mr. Malarek, when you
write something new,
we'll pay you for it.

12:38.457 --> 12:41.794
But from now on,
when you write nothing,
we pay nothing.

12:45.130 --> 12:46.832
Did I just get fired? No, no.

12:46.966 --> 12:48.367
You're just gonna be
freelance.

12:49.001 --> 12:53.139
Oh, Art, come on.
You can't make me a stringer.
I just had a baby.

12:53.272 --> 12:55.841
Why don't you just let me
give you regular
assignments, that's it?

12:55.975 --> 12:57.777
I don't do
regular assignments.

12:57.910 --> 13:01.680
Ha! Okay. But your mind's
in 93 orbits at once.

13:01.813 --> 13:03.815
You just gotta
land on something.
I don't give a shit.

13:03.949 --> 13:06.151
Pick an easy subject.
You do one story a week,

13:06.285 --> 13:08.119
you make the exact
same money. That's it.

13:08.253 --> 13:09.554
[sighs]

13:10.355 --> 13:12.391
Look, Art, it's not
about the money, all right?

13:12.524 --> 13:13.826
It's about my process.

13:13.959 --> 13:15.627
All right.

13:15.761 --> 13:18.931
You and you process
get together,
do one story a week.

13:22.033 --> 13:23.435
I'd like to cash this.

13:24.836 --> 13:28.140
Twenty, 40, 60, 80, 100...

13:50.095 --> 13:52.131
There you go. Cheers, man.

13:54.099 --> 13:55.868
What can I get for you?

13:56.702 --> 13:57.802
Directions.

13:57.936 --> 13:59.805
What do you mean
by directions?

14:00.405 --> 14:02.374
Looking for a guy
called Michael.

14:14.753 --> 14:17.756
Gentlemen, it is my true
honor to be here today.

14:18.390 --> 14:21.393
And I welcome the chance to work
with each and every one of you.

14:22.060 --> 14:23.662
But make no mistake.

14:24.196 --> 14:26.832
We are all soldiers
in a war on drugs.

14:27.433 --> 14:30.035
The last few years
have been...

15:17.515 --> 15:20.552
["In the Air Tonight"
by Phil Collins playing
on stereo]

15:23.689 --> 15:25.924
Daniel! Bro.

15:26.825 --> 15:29.027
Hey, man, this is the guy
I'm telling you about,

15:29.160 --> 15:31.597
my best friend,
Daniel, man.

15:33.031 --> 15:34.333
[in French]

15:36.735 --> 15:39.405
[in English] Hey, Glen!
This is fucking Daniel.

15:43.809 --> 15:47.579
Glen! This is the guy, man.
You know, my trip to Thailand.

15:49.648 --> 15:51.150
Thailand? Yeah.

15:53.184 --> 15:54.519
Thailand party guy?

15:54.653 --> 15:58.157
Fucking A, man!
The Thailand party guy.

15:58.656 --> 16:00.025
Holy shit.

16:00.159 --> 16:01.926
Hey, Thailand
party guy.

16:02.427 --> 16:05.998
I'm the BC party guy.
Small fucking world, huh?

16:06.131 --> 16:07.399
Small as shit.

16:07.532 --> 16:10.168
Fuck. There's something
I want to show you.

16:10.301 --> 16:13.572
Uh, Aimee, get him a beer.

16:14.973 --> 16:16.774
Thailand party guy,
come over here.

16:17.242 --> 16:19.211
Hey, bro, you, uh,
you still owe me money

16:19.345 --> 16:21.813
for the work I did
on the boat, remember?

16:22.246 --> 16:23.915
[Glen] The fuck I do.

16:24.049 --> 16:25.284
Where is it?

16:28.019 --> 16:29.821
Where the fuck is it?

16:30.288 --> 16:32.324
Where the fuck is it?

16:32.457 --> 16:34.593
And what the fuck
are you doing on my boat?

16:34.727 --> 16:35.794
I... [Michael] Hey, whoa.

16:35.927 --> 16:37.128
He just got here, man.

16:37.262 --> 16:38.697
He's my buddy. Remember?

16:39.531 --> 16:41.533
Oh, he's your buddy? Yeah.

16:41.666 --> 16:45.103
What the fuck are you
asking me for money?
I owe you?

16:45.237 --> 16:47.071
No, no! I was kidding.
Man, I was just kidding.

16:47.205 --> 16:49.474
You piece of shit!
Where is my shit?

16:49.607 --> 16:52.311
It's probably in the bedroom
where you leave all your stuff.

16:53.177 --> 16:55.014
Oh, fuck. It is.

16:55.547 --> 16:57.415
[laughing] Shit.

16:57.549 --> 17:01.320
You guys looked like
you were gonna fucking
shit your pants.

17:01.453 --> 17:04.123
[laughing]

17:05.391 --> 17:06.425
Fuck.

17:08.060 --> 17:09.428
Give me a second.

17:12.097 --> 17:13.398
Aimee.

17:14.066 --> 17:16.535
Are you gonna fucking
kiss her or what?

17:18.670 --> 17:20.105
[sighs]

17:31.917 --> 17:33.752
[in English] Relax, man.

17:34.085 --> 17:35.687
[Glen] Found it.

17:37.288 --> 17:40.325
Ah! This is what
I wanna show you, Thai boy.

17:40.725 --> 17:42.327
This...

17:43.461 --> 17:45.097
Oh!

17:49.001 --> 17:53.305
Now, Michael tells me
you brought some
Thai number four into BC.

17:55.473 --> 17:57.142
He told you that, huh?

17:58.677 --> 18:00.112
Shit.

18:00.912 --> 18:02.213
I'd love to taste that.

18:02.347 --> 18:06.584
I mean, you can't find
that shit anywhere here.

18:06.718 --> 18:09.021
All right, I gotta go. Whoa, whoa, whoa.

18:09.154 --> 18:10.989
What the fuck?

18:11.123 --> 18:14.659
I only bring this shit out
for special people.
Ask Michael.

18:14.792 --> 18:16.161
Fuckin' A. True, man.

18:16.761 --> 18:20.765
By the way, this smackity-yak
is, like, 90% pure.

18:20.899 --> 18:22.701
W-W-Well, close enough.

18:22.834 --> 18:25.404
[laughing]

18:27.272 --> 18:28.673
I don't shoot up, so...

18:28.807 --> 18:31.577
That's cool, that's cool.
I don't wanna die either.

18:31.710 --> 18:33.878
♪ Coming in the air
Tonight... ♪

18:34.012 --> 18:35.848
That's why I like to smoke it.

18:37.048 --> 18:38.484
Give me the lighter.

18:39.284 --> 18:40.719
Fucking...

18:42.453 --> 18:45.124
♪ For all my life ♪

18:45.791 --> 18:47.626
♪ Oh, Lord ♪

18:49.394 --> 18:52.764
♪ I can feel it
In the air tonight ♪

18:52.898 --> 18:54.233
♪ Oh, Lord ♪

18:54.799 --> 18:55.800
[moans]

18:55.934 --> 18:58.170
♪ Oh, Lord... ♪

18:59.671 --> 19:03.041
I appreciate it, man,
but I'm okay.

19:03.175 --> 19:05.843
Oh, you think you're
too good for my shit?

19:05.977 --> 19:07.578
♪ Oh, Lord ♪

19:07.712 --> 19:08.814
[sighs]

19:09.248 --> 19:12.451
♪ I can feel it coming
In the air tonight... ♪

19:12.584 --> 19:15.254
Ain't no place
you gotta be but heaven.

19:16.421 --> 19:18.156
I'll let you in on a secret.

19:18.790 --> 19:21.527
If you're really nice
to these two angels...

19:22.728 --> 19:25.430
they'll smoke the paper
off your joint.

19:25.964 --> 19:27.899
♪ Oh, Lord ♪

19:28.033 --> 19:29.634
Mmm...

19:29.768 --> 19:33.738
♪ I can feel it
In the air tonight ♪

19:33.872 --> 19:35.606
♪ Oh, Lord ♪

19:35.740 --> 19:38.944
♪ Oh, Lord
Oh, Lord ♪

19:39.745 --> 19:43.215
♪ Well, I've been waiting
For this moment... ♪

19:44.081 --> 19:45.350
How long has it been?

19:46.384 --> 19:48.820
♪ Oh, Lord
Oh, Lord ♪

19:50.889 --> 19:52.591
Six months.

19:54.092 --> 19:55.861
[Glen]
Welcome home, friend.

20:11.142 --> 20:12.176
Art.

20:12.610 --> 20:14.279
Big-time drug dealer.
Real prick, this guy.

20:14.412 --> 20:16.047
Gets arrested in Bangkok,
but when he's arrested--

20:16.181 --> 20:19.184
Right. Police officer dies.
We already covered the story.

20:19.318 --> 20:20.752
Do you actually read
your own newspaper?

20:20.886 --> 20:22.554
You guys covered
a 50-word press release.

20:22.688 --> 20:24.389
I do a two-parter,
bring in all the background.

20:24.522 --> 20:26.224
How does the international
heroin trade work?

20:26.358 --> 20:28.827
I mean, how does the shit get
from Thailand into our country?

20:28.960 --> 20:31.462
Right. Pull a bunch
of drug-trade stats
anyone can get.

20:31.596 --> 20:33.097
No, no. No. I don't think so.

20:33.231 --> 20:36.301
I put flesh on it, all right?
An agent killed in the line.

20:36.434 --> 20:38.269
Who is this
badass drug dealer?

20:38.403 --> 20:39.737
Two North Americans
meet their fates

20:39.871 --> 20:42.174
halfway around the world
in Bangkok, right?

20:42.307 --> 20:43.808
Deliver it
by Saturday?

20:43.942 --> 20:46.345
Saturday? Sure.
Saturday and Sunday.
It's a two-parter.

20:46.478 --> 20:48.680
Yeah. Two parts, two paychecks.

20:49.581 --> 20:52.818
Okay. Did you just
double your salary?

20:54.285 --> 20:55.887
[sighs]

21:03.161 --> 21:04.997
[inhales]

21:06.164 --> 21:07.666
[sighs]

21:36.261 --> 21:37.829
[coughs]

21:54.479 --> 21:56.648
Ah. He's alive.
[chuckles]

21:56.781 --> 21:58.216
Hey, have you
seen Michael?

21:58.349 --> 22:00.385
Yeah, he left
a couple hours ago.

22:00.519 --> 22:03.055
Taking a bus
back to Montreal.

22:04.622 --> 22:07.224
Shit. Did that cocksucker
take some cash from you?

22:07.525 --> 22:10.329
Some cash? He took
everything I had.

22:11.329 --> 22:12.731
You can't
trust a junkie.

22:13.531 --> 22:15.700
[sighs] Dude, uh,

22:15.833 --> 22:17.569
we got clients coming
in ten minutes,

22:17.702 --> 22:20.338
and you kind of look
like run-over dog shit.

22:20.472 --> 22:22.306
Yeah. I'm sorry.
I'll get out of your way.

22:22.440 --> 22:24.909
No, I said
we got clients.

22:25.042 --> 22:26.511
You want a job?

22:27.411 --> 22:29.447
Oh, man.
I-I appreciate the offer,

22:29.581 --> 22:31.749
but I don't know
anything about fishing.

22:31.883 --> 22:34.185
Plus, I gotta-- I gotta
find a place to stay.

22:34.319 --> 22:35.820
You can stay
in the cabin.

22:35.954 --> 22:37.388
It's small,
but what the fuck?

22:37.522 --> 22:38.924
It's free, right?

22:40.192 --> 22:41.292
You serious?

22:41.426 --> 22:43.094
As a heart attack.

22:43.695 --> 22:45.596
I've had my tough times.

22:45.730 --> 22:49.367
Just put on a shirt.
It's not a gay cruise.

22:49.501 --> 22:51.837
Pays $80 a day,
plus tips.

22:53.371 --> 22:54.606
Okay.

23:26.237 --> 23:27.338
[man] Victor.

23:27.472 --> 23:29.674
Sergeant. Surprise visit.

23:29.808 --> 23:32.810
I'm doing an in-depth
piece for The Globe.

23:32.944 --> 23:35.413
I thought a live interview
could make it more human.

23:35.547 --> 23:37.115
Do you mind?

23:37.849 --> 23:39.584
There have been
no news items released today.

23:39.718 --> 23:42.053
I'm thinking an oldie,
but a goodie.

23:42.186 --> 23:46.224
What are your thoughts
on the Thailand bust?

23:46.358 --> 23:47.826
Was the whole thing
worth it?

23:47.959 --> 23:50.829
It's a tragedy.
That's all I can say.

23:50.962 --> 23:53.164
Yeah, but, I mean,
you guys must be in shock.

23:53.298 --> 23:55.634
Well, you can say that again.

23:56.868 --> 23:59.137
Now, come on, Bill.
Throw me a quote here.

23:59.270 --> 24:01.372
Anything I can use
other than, "It's a tragedy"?

24:01.506 --> 24:03.775
Well, the point of
an operation like this

24:03.908 --> 24:06.344
is to make Canada
a safer place.

24:06.478 --> 24:09.514
Now, a major heroin pipeline
was shut down.

24:09.648 --> 24:11.883
And when an officer
dies in the line of duty,

24:12.016 --> 24:15.454
it's a sad reminder of how
dangerous this job really is.

24:15.821 --> 24:17.088
Okay.

24:18.890 --> 24:20.725
I read the press release.

24:20.859 --> 24:23.494
But this asshole you arrested,
why is he still in Thailand?

24:23.627 --> 24:27.332
We were invited only
to assist the Thai police
for this operation, Malarek.

24:27.465 --> 24:30.569
He'll be prosecuted there. But what's
this prick's story?

24:30.702 --> 24:33.238
Everything's in
the press release. Nothing's in the press release.

24:33.371 --> 24:35.940
Who is this guy?
How long has this guy been
running heroin out of BC?

24:36.074 --> 24:37.709
I don't have
any more comments.

24:37.842 --> 24:39.610
The matter is before
the courts in Bangkok, okay?

24:39.744 --> 24:43.381
I'm not allowed to discuss
the intricacies of this,
especially with you.

24:43.514 --> 24:44.783
That's it?

24:47.419 --> 24:48.887
Thanks, Sergeant.

24:54.693 --> 24:56.628
[Daniel] All right,
keep it going, guys.

24:59.097 --> 25:01.900
[chattering]

25:04.269 --> 25:05.704
Here you go.

25:10.441 --> 25:12.643
Oh, my God.
Those guys loved you.

25:13.077 --> 25:16.882
They even left you
an extra tip.

25:19.184 --> 25:20.952
Or we could do...

25:21.752 --> 25:23.154
the trade again.

25:23.454 --> 25:24.890
Your call.

25:26.791 --> 25:28.193
You know,
I was thinking...

25:30.828 --> 25:33.331
if I play
my cards right,

25:33.798 --> 25:35.466
this could be
my boat soon.

25:35.600 --> 25:37.035
Yeah?

25:37.869 --> 25:39.370
Hell, we could be partners,

25:39.503 --> 25:41.273
make some
real money.

25:42.373 --> 25:44.142
-You serious?
-Yeah.

25:45.744 --> 25:47.579
It's funny how
things work out.

25:47.712 --> 25:49.480
I can't tell you
how much I appreciate

25:49.614 --> 25:51.449
everything you've done for me.

25:51.583 --> 25:52.883
Hey, uh, don't
smoke that yet.

25:53.017 --> 25:54.786
I need a ride
to the airport.

25:54.919 --> 25:56.621
The airport?
Where you going?

25:57.989 --> 25:59.256
Colombia.

25:59.924 --> 26:02.027
Got a meeting, last minute.

26:07.765 --> 26:09.300
All right.

26:10.068 --> 26:13.037
Shit, I almost
forgot to ask you.
Can you do me a favor?

26:13.170 --> 26:16.240
Go to that address,
uh, ask for Mary.

26:16.374 --> 26:18.843
She has a package.
Can you grab it for me?

26:18.977 --> 26:21.445
And if you could just
hold onto it till I get back.

26:21.579 --> 26:23.114
You got it. Thanks.

26:23.348 --> 26:24.382
[grunts]

26:24.649 --> 26:26.051
Have a safe trip.

26:58.583 --> 26:59.985
[grunts]

27:03.621 --> 27:06.391
A plane ticket
to go to Bangkok?
Are you out of your mind?

27:06.524 --> 27:07.726
We need an interview. With who?

27:08.660 --> 27:10.628
The Canadian drug dealer. You wanna call Louise yourself,

27:10.762 --> 27:13.464
ask her for a budget
to go to Thailand?
'Cause I ain't doing that, pal.

27:13.598 --> 27:15.933
Give me two days over there
and I'll come back with
a Globe and Mail exclusive

27:16.067 --> 27:17.868
that looks like
a national scandal. Wait, wait--

27:18.002 --> 27:19.804
It'll be huge,
above the fold, front page.

27:19.938 --> 27:21.572
Hold on. Then hit her
with the budget.

27:21.705 --> 27:24.008
When did this
easy paycheck feature
become a national scandal?

27:24.142 --> 27:25.576
Don't blame me if
I'm the only guy here

27:25.710 --> 27:27.244
who can see through
police bullshit.

27:27.378 --> 27:29.480
I didn't even start asking
the guy the real questions

27:29.614 --> 27:32.517
when he hit me with
a line of "no comment"-- Fine, you've got a hunch.

27:32.651 --> 27:33.984
Do like everyone else
in the newsroom--

27:34.118 --> 27:36.020
make the calls,
pull the clippings,

27:36.154 --> 27:38.789
check computer databases-- I checked with all
of my sources.

27:38.923 --> 27:40.792
No one's ever heard of
this huge drug kingpin,

27:40.925 --> 27:42.827
and nobody knows anything
about this pipeline of heroin

27:42.960 --> 27:46.030
that's coming into the country. I don't have five grand
to put on this, so...

27:46.164 --> 27:47.966
Wait a minute.
Did the feds call you?

27:48.099 --> 27:50.901
Are you on their payroll now?
Is that what's going on?

27:51.435 --> 27:53.071
Get into my office!

27:53.204 --> 27:54.406
Yeah, all right.

28:00.545 --> 28:03.447
Come on, relax, Art.
You know how I get when I find
something juicy like this.

28:03.581 --> 28:05.683
You wanna go? Yeah.

28:05.816 --> 28:09.387
I'm paying for your trip.
But if you don't come back with
a front-page story, you're gone.

28:09.520 --> 28:13.892
Okay. Okay? Louise will never publish
anything from you again.

28:14.459 --> 28:15.493
Got it.

28:15.627 --> 28:16.961
Thanks, Art.

28:39.517 --> 28:40.919
Hmm.

28:44.255 --> 28:46.591
Pigging down already, Picker?

28:47.058 --> 28:50.195
You guys are the ones
that are 45 minutes late.

28:53.097 --> 28:54.799
Two coffees, please.

28:55.232 --> 28:56.800
Can we have this all
on one check?

28:56.934 --> 28:58.469
And, um, they're paying.

28:58.602 --> 29:00.104
Of course. Thanks.

29:00.237 --> 29:01.238
[inhales]

29:01.372 --> 29:04.409
That ass! Get me
a fork and knife, right?

29:07.345 --> 29:09.680
Well, you guys must be
humping some dry ice

29:09.814 --> 29:11.416
if you're sitting here
with me, huh?

29:12.150 --> 29:13.618
How's the fishing business?

29:13.751 --> 29:18.455
Great. Lately, I've been
fishing in international waters.

29:19.123 --> 29:20.858
A lot of big fish out there.

29:20.992 --> 29:22.994
What do you mean
by "international"?

29:23.127 --> 29:27.165
How do you guys feel about
the term "Golden Triangle"?

29:28.232 --> 29:30.135
You know people
in Thailand?

29:30.701 --> 29:32.203
You know what?

29:33.904 --> 29:36.440
I think I'm barking
up the wrong tree.

29:36.574 --> 29:38.342
This is too big for you guys.

29:38.476 --> 29:40.077
What are we talking
about here, Picker?

29:40.211 --> 29:42.914
We're talking about
international players.

29:43.047 --> 29:48.753
We're talking about 99% pure H
from Thailand to BC.

29:48.887 --> 29:51.288
Most importantly,
we're talking about you guys

29:51.422 --> 29:54.324
paying me more
than my normal source fee.

29:54.458 --> 29:57.528
You're saying you can
get this guy for us?

29:57.662 --> 30:00.532
No. I'm saying
I got this guy.

30:06.470 --> 30:07.972
[door rattles]

30:47.745 --> 30:49.214
Pleasure doing business.

30:50.048 --> 30:51.449
[in French]

30:53.017 --> 30:54.018
[chuckles]

30:54.152 --> 30:55.854
[in English] Cool.

31:17.941 --> 31:19.177
Hey, uh...

31:21.545 --> 31:23.181
[sighs]

31:46.304 --> 31:48.539
[man]
I thought you didn't want
to work with this guy, uh...

31:48.672 --> 31:51.008
[man 2] Picker.
He came to us with this.

31:51.142 --> 31:54.144
The target is importing
from Thailand.

31:54.278 --> 31:57.348
[man]
Well, this Léger character
seems like a big fish.

31:58.315 --> 32:00.851
Comes out of the system
as Code A. He's connected.

32:00.985 --> 32:04.188
[man 2] Criminal records show
he's tied to the Hells.

32:05.423 --> 32:08.292
Why, uh-- Why don't you
walk me through this thing,
okay?

32:08.425 --> 32:10.461
Like, break it down
into boxes for me.

32:10.595 --> 32:12.362
What's the outcome box?

32:12.496 --> 32:15.666
Do you see yourself taking down
this target in Thailand? No.

32:15.799 --> 32:19.069
We collect the evidence
under the auspices
of the Thai police,

32:19.203 --> 32:21.672
and we participate
in the buy.

32:21.805 --> 32:23.474
Léger goes home.

32:23.607 --> 32:25.243
The outcome box:

32:26.010 --> 32:28.947
We arrest Léger
at Vancouver Airport.

32:31.782 --> 32:33.217
All right, Sergeant.

32:34.385 --> 32:36.187
I'm gonna go ahead
and authorize the operation,

32:36.320 --> 32:38.723
but the maximum
the source can get
is 80 grand.

32:40.090 --> 32:41.625
Plus expenses.

32:41.759 --> 32:44.295
I'll talk to Picker. Good.

32:49.199 --> 32:51.102
[upbeat song playing]

32:55.773 --> 32:59.310
[man singing in Thai on radio]

33:00.578 --> 33:01.980
[sighs]

33:04.849 --> 33:06.351
Thank you. Thank you.

33:15.393 --> 33:17.395
[man] I'm sorry, Mr. Malarek.

33:17.829 --> 33:19.330
I cannot allow you in, sir.

33:20.998 --> 33:22.966
All right, look.

33:23.267 --> 33:24.435
We both know
Canadian citizens

33:24.568 --> 33:26.370
are allowed to visit
Canadian inmates.

33:26.504 --> 33:29.574
And that's a
Canadian passport, so...

33:29.707 --> 33:33.344
The passport is not a problem,
but I cannot let you in.

33:33.711 --> 33:34.778
Why the hell not?

33:34.912 --> 33:36.580
Have a nice day,
sir.

33:36.713 --> 33:38.282
[speaking Thai]

33:38.882 --> 33:40.685
[phone line beeping]

33:43.954 --> 33:45.723
[beeping continues]

33:48.125 --> 33:51.928
[man] Hello, Mr. Malarek?
I'm Jim Raiven, the embassy's
federal agent in Thailand.

33:52.062 --> 33:55.666
How can I help you? Uh, I'm here in Bangkok
to see, uh,

33:55.800 --> 33:58.836
a Canadian prisoner
you guys arrested,
and I went to the prison, and--

33:58.969 --> 34:01.138
This case is still under
investigation, Mr. Malarek,

34:01.271 --> 34:05.076
as I'm sure my colleague
in Toronto told you.

34:06.643 --> 34:09.247
Did the embassy
put me on a blacklist
at Bombat prison?

34:09.380 --> 34:12.183
I suggest you read
the press release
on Operation Goliath

34:12.316 --> 34:15.219
like everyone else, Mr. Malarek. You know what?
I've been here many times.

34:15.353 --> 34:18.355
I know how the system works.
I know the embassy
doesn't have any right--

34:18.489 --> 34:20.591
Have a nice day, Mr. Malarek.

34:20.724 --> 34:22.093
[line clicks]

34:23.494 --> 34:24.629
Hello?

34:25.162 --> 34:26.764
[dial tone]

34:33.204 --> 34:34.539
Fuck.

34:36.740 --> 34:38.209
All right.

34:38.342 --> 34:41.579
["Respect" by Aretha Franklin
playing on stereo]

34:46.984 --> 34:50.254
♪ What you want
Baby, I got it ♪

34:51.389 --> 34:55.259
♪ What you need
You know I got it ♪

34:55.393 --> 34:58.963
♪ All I'm asking is
For a little respect
When you come home ♪

34:59.096 --> 35:01.732
♪ Just a little bit ♪ ♪ Hey, baby ♪

35:01.866 --> 35:04.601
♪ When you get home ♪ ♪ Just a little bit ♪

35:04.735 --> 35:07.004
♪ Mister ♪ ♪ Just a little bit... ♪

35:07.238 --> 35:11.142
[in French]

35:15.646 --> 35:17.581
De toute façon,
[in English]
we're partners now, baby.

35:17.714 --> 35:20.351
What's his is mine,
and what's mine is his.

35:21.118 --> 35:22.720
All right, then.

35:23.988 --> 35:25.956
[sighs, sniffles]

35:26.390 --> 35:28.125
♪ Just a little bit ♪

35:28.592 --> 35:32.663
♪ I'm about to give you
All my money ♪

35:33.130 --> 35:34.098
♪ And all I'm asking ♪

35:34.231 --> 35:35.366
[phone ringing]

35:35.499 --> 35:36.967
♪ In return, honey ♪

35:37.601 --> 35:41.205
♪ Is to give me my propers
When you get home ♪

35:42.473 --> 35:43.874
[ringing continues]

35:44.008 --> 35:45.676
♪ When you get home ♪

35:45.809 --> 35:46.878
[music stops]

35:48.246 --> 35:49.413
Yeah?

35:49.547 --> 35:51.115
Why don't you answer
the phone?

35:51.248 --> 35:52.749
Hey, man! How's your trip?

35:52.883 --> 35:55.352
I'm stuck in Jamaica,
but I'm coming back tomorrow.

35:55.486 --> 35:57.120
I need you to pick me up
at the airport.

35:57.254 --> 35:59.089
What are you doing in Jamaica?

35:59.223 --> 36:00.558
That's none of your business.

36:00.691 --> 36:03.060
Your business is to pick me up
tomorrow at 9:00.

36:03.194 --> 36:05.228
-Oh, and, Danny Boy.
-Yeah?

36:05.362 --> 36:08.432
Answer the phone
when I fucking call, okay?

36:15.038 --> 36:17.340
[man] Thank you for
the signed copy of your book.

36:17.474 --> 36:19.043
My wife, she's so proud.

36:19.176 --> 36:21.512
[Victor] You're welcome.
I'm here with The Globe.

36:21.646 --> 36:24.848
I'm writing an article
on an Operation Goliath.
Have you heard of it?

36:24.982 --> 36:27.284
[man] The Canadian drug dealer
who was arrested.

36:27.417 --> 36:30.854
[Victor] Exactly.
The prison manager won't
let me in to see him.

36:30.988 --> 36:33.624
-Why not?
-I was hoping you could
tell me that.

36:34.491 --> 36:36.727
The Canadian police seem
to have restricted my access.

36:36.860 --> 36:40.030
You should see
my friend Jim Raiven

36:40.164 --> 36:41.565
at the Canadian embassy.

36:41.699 --> 36:43.834
I'll get you in touch. Sergeant Jim Raiven?

36:43.967 --> 36:45.369
You know him?

36:46.103 --> 36:47.437
[sighs]

36:47.571 --> 36:48.705
He's a Canadian officer.

36:48.839 --> 36:50.708
He doesn't have
the power to decide

36:50.841 --> 36:53.110
whether or not I see
a prisoner here in Bangkok.

36:53.244 --> 36:55.112
You're a good friend,
Victor.

36:55.246 --> 36:58.082
But the Thai police has
a special relationship
with your country.

36:58.215 --> 37:03.421
My hands are tied.
I-I must ask that
you go through Jim Raiven.

37:04.255 --> 37:06.189
Okay.

37:06.323 --> 37:08.225
But my readers are gonna be
very confused.

37:08.358 --> 37:11.828
What do you mean? When I write about this,
they're gonna want to know

37:11.962 --> 37:15.499
how a Canadian sergeant
was able to order around
General Suchart

37:15.633 --> 37:17.668
of the Royal Thai Police
on his own soil.

37:22.873 --> 37:24.408
You cannot write that.

37:26.209 --> 37:28.879
[phone ringing]

37:42.559 --> 37:44.662
[ringing continues]

37:45.462 --> 37:47.698
[panting]

37:49.867 --> 37:50.634
Cooper?

37:50.768 --> 37:53.371
We're a go.  How much?

37:53.970 --> 37:55.072
Your end is 60.

37:55.206 --> 37:56.774
Are you fucking kidding me?

37:56.907 --> 37:59.343
I get 40
for delivering lowlifes.

37:59.477 --> 38:01.411
Call me when you
have a serious offer.

38:01.544 --> 38:02.979
How much do you want?

38:03.380 --> 38:04.781
One hundred.

38:04.915 --> 38:06.350
I'll give you 80.

38:06.483 --> 38:08.552
Forty now,
40 when Léger goes down.

38:08.685 --> 38:12.022
For that price,
I'm gonna need expenses.  Sure.

38:12.556 --> 38:17.061
But the deal is effective
only if you can start
before the end of the month.

38:18.062 --> 38:19.397
Fine.

38:29.740 --> 38:31.842
Hey, guys. Come over here.

38:32.242 --> 38:33.778
Hey, how's it going?

38:33.911 --> 38:35.345
Beautiful day, huh?

38:35.478 --> 38:36.580
[speaks Spanish]

38:36.714 --> 38:38.849
I was just
talking to my wife.

38:38.983 --> 38:40.150
My wife, pregnant.

38:40.283 --> 38:41.385
I'm gonna be a father.
Padre.

38:41.518 --> 38:43.354
- Papá.
-Yeah!

38:43.487 --> 38:45.256
Hey, will you celebrate with me?

38:45.389 --> 38:46.790
Come have a cigar. Please.

38:46.923 --> 38:49.426
Trabajo. Come on, come on.
Por favor.

38:49.560 --> 38:51.094
[Cooper] Léger is gonna be
target number one

38:51.228 --> 38:54.464
on the priority scale
of the month, coast to coast.

38:54.597 --> 38:58.668
We're gonna be the only
international undercover
operation approved so far.

38:58.802 --> 39:03.707
If we nail it, we are gonna get
the biggest budget the division
will spend this year.

39:03.840 --> 39:05.375
Are you saying
we're going to Thailand?

39:05.509 --> 39:07.210
We're going to Thailand!

39:07.944 --> 39:10.014
-Can you take off your coat?
Take off your coat.
-No, no.

39:10.147 --> 39:14.384
I want my wife to know that
I'm having a good time. Come on.

39:14.518 --> 39:17.922
"Celebrate-io."
Okay, now come here.

39:18.455 --> 39:19.790
All right.

39:20.323 --> 39:22.693
Look mean. Yeah.

39:22.827 --> 39:24.728
All right, that's good.
Beat it. Got it.

39:24.861 --> 39:26.429
Oh, my God!
I wish you were there.

39:26.563 --> 39:28.665
It was fucking crazy.
I was at this party.

39:28.798 --> 39:31.869
It was insane.
These fucking women
were so beautiful.

39:32.002 --> 39:34.204
And I got in an argument
with this fucking nigger.

39:34.337 --> 39:35.773
He's fucking
threatening me,

39:35.906 --> 39:38.408
so I take a Magnum .45
and I stick it right here.

39:38.541 --> 39:40.577
Look! Right here.
He's all quiet.

39:40.710 --> 39:42.379
Look at this.
See that guy?

39:42.513 --> 39:46.150
That's a motherfucking
Colombian drug lord.

39:46.283 --> 39:50.454
This guy is so fucking powerful
and my friend now.

39:50.587 --> 39:53.624
He makes so much fucking money.
And so will we.

39:57.961 --> 40:01.799
Daniel.
Where'd you put the package
I asked you to pick up?

40:01.932 --> 40:04.501
Oh, I didn't think it was safe
on the boat with the clients,

40:04.635 --> 40:06.971
so I'm, uh, keeping it
at a friend's house.

40:07.104 --> 40:08.472
Go get it. Yeah.

40:08.605 --> 40:09.940
I got people
who want to buy it.

40:10.073 --> 40:11.542
Yeah, of course.

40:40.470 --> 40:42.039
[grunting]

40:44.241 --> 40:45.676
[sniffles]

41:07.197 --> 41:08.298
[grunts]

41:08.431 --> 41:09.833
Ah!

41:09.966 --> 41:11.869
-[Glen] He was robbed?
-Yeah.

41:12.002 --> 41:15.539
Fucking kicked his ass,
but he swears
he doesn't have it anymore.

41:16.206 --> 41:17.607
What's his name?

41:17.741 --> 41:19.609
Doesn't matter.
He got robbed.

41:19.743 --> 41:22.980
-You're so full of shit.
-I'm telling you.

41:23.113 --> 41:28.852
Yeah, I'm telling you
to tell your friend
he owes me 1,000 bucks.

41:28.985 --> 41:31.522
And every day he's late,
40 points interest.

41:31.655 --> 41:33.323
400 a day?

41:33.457 --> 41:35.225
-He can't afford it?
-Fuck no!

41:35.358 --> 41:39.196
Well then, he better
find that thousand real quick.

41:43.000 --> 41:44.268
Jesus.

42:02.652 --> 42:04.922
[horn honking]

42:14.264 --> 42:16.133
[phone ringing]

42:23.707 --> 42:25.275
Yeah? [Arthur] Hey.

42:25.409 --> 42:27.011
Dave Miller scooped you.

42:27.144 --> 42:29.746
What?  Yeah, he met with
your guy already.

42:29.879 --> 42:31.314
It'll be in The Sun tomorrow.

42:31.448 --> 42:32.849
Well, did you read
the article?

42:32.982 --> 42:34.551
No, not yet.
But it doesn't matter

42:34.685 --> 42:36.486
'cause we don't have
the exclusive anymore.

42:36.620 --> 42:37.954
I just threatened
the general in charge of

42:38.088 --> 42:39.556
the Thai Narcotic
Suppression Bureau

42:39.689 --> 42:41.358
to get in to see this guy.

42:41.491 --> 42:44.060
I know, but... I'm writing
my fucking article.

42:44.194 --> 42:46.429
You can put it on
the front page or not.

42:46.563 --> 42:48.332
Just stay close to your fax.

42:50.667 --> 42:52.269
Oh, and how much
for this?

42:52.803 --> 42:54.572
No, don't need
the helmet.

42:56.240 --> 42:58.809
[in French]

43:19.163 --> 43:20.664
Where's your bike?

43:25.903 --> 43:27.671
This looks light.

43:29.206 --> 43:30.541
$350.

43:30.674 --> 43:32.576
This doesn't even
cover the interest.

43:32.709 --> 43:34.511
Keep my tips
for the next month.

43:34.645 --> 43:36.814
Jesus, would you give me
a fucking break?

43:36.947 --> 43:40.951
I gave you a place to stay.
I gave you a motherfucking job.

43:41.084 --> 43:44.254
When you felt like shit,
I gave you the best dope in BC.

43:44.387 --> 43:45.422
I know, but every t--

43:45.556 --> 43:47.123
Don't "but" me! [groans]

43:47.257 --> 43:50.394
I don't want "but,"
"if," "please."

43:50.527 --> 43:52.429
And no bullshit!

43:52.562 --> 43:54.932
Business is business.

43:57.267 --> 44:00.137
Look, I fucked up, okay?
I'm sorry.

44:00.270 --> 44:01.972
I trusted you.

44:02.106 --> 44:05.175
Now I need all that
trust shit built back up.

44:07.810 --> 44:09.246
Here's the deal.

44:10.847 --> 44:12.216
You do this thing
for me,

