going on here?

1:13:41.550 --> 1:13:43.251
Well, he robbed
a gas station.

1:13:43.385 --> 1:13:44.486
What?

1:13:44.620 --> 1:13:46.421
He robbed
a gas station.

1:13:46.555 --> 1:13:49.291
So, I don't know.
He's not as innocent
as you might think.

1:13:49.424 --> 1:13:51.326
Oh, he robbed
a gas station? Yeah.

1:13:51.460 --> 1:13:52.828
So that gives
the federal police the right

1:13:52.961 --> 1:13:54.763
to leave him in Thailand
to get the death penalty.

1:13:54.896 --> 1:13:56.598
That makes a lot
of fucking sense.

1:13:56.732 --> 1:13:58.433
Meanwhile,
they can cover up
their colossal clusterfuck

1:13:58.566 --> 1:14:00.702
because the media
is sitting here sucking
its collective dick

1:14:00.836 --> 1:14:02.504
all because the victim's
not a nice guy?

1:14:02.638 --> 1:14:05.573
Would you just relax?
Did I say I wasn't gonna run
the story? No.

1:14:05.707 --> 1:14:07.609
I'm having it
checked first, all right?

1:14:07.742 --> 1:14:10.044
Why are you making
this thing personal?

1:14:10.178 --> 1:14:12.780
Lawyer's at 3:00.
Make the necessary cuts.

1:14:12.914 --> 1:14:14.482
It'll run tomorrow, all right?

1:14:14.616 --> 1:14:16.585
On Page 5?
Below the fold?

1:14:16.718 --> 1:14:18.987
No follow-up?
Everyone moves on?

1:14:19.587 --> 1:14:22.824
Meanwhile, a Canadian citizen
is executed in
a fucking third-world country,

1:14:22.958 --> 1:14:25.994
and we're not gonna do
a fucking thing about it, Art?

1:14:26.494 --> 1:14:27.830
I'm sorry.

1:14:34.870 --> 1:14:37.005
You know how you gave me
my first story?

1:14:38.039 --> 1:14:40.341
You made me the journalist
I am today.

1:14:40.475 --> 1:14:42.044
I never thanked you
for that.

1:14:44.912 --> 1:14:46.581
Can you have somebody
just put my stuff in a box?

1:14:46.715 --> 1:14:48.082
I'll pick it up tomorrow. Come on, Vic.

1:14:48.216 --> 1:14:50.018
No, you guys aren't
into my stuff anymore.

1:14:50.152 --> 1:14:52.855
I should have heard you
when you said it last week.

1:15:12.507 --> 1:15:13.909
[elevator door opens]

1:15:47.609 --> 1:15:49.645
Hey. Hi.

1:15:51.413 --> 1:15:55.150
Um, I'm a friend of Daniel's,
and I know you guys
know each other,

1:15:55.283 --> 1:15:57.552
and I'm looking for him,
but I don't know where he is.

1:15:57.685 --> 1:15:59.154
Do you know where
I can find him?

1:16:00.121 --> 1:16:01.189
No.

1:16:02.024 --> 1:16:04.092
So you're telling me
you don't know him?

1:16:04.225 --> 1:16:06.928
No, I'm telling you
I have no idea where he is.

1:16:07.062 --> 1:16:10.766
Oh. All fucking
and no talking, huh?

1:16:10.899 --> 1:16:13.034
Wow. Would you be
my girlfriend?

1:16:13.167 --> 1:16:14.369
All right.

1:16:14.503 --> 1:16:16.204
Hey, hey.
Hey, hey, hey.

1:16:23.311 --> 1:16:25.581
How's your little
side business going?

1:16:38.026 --> 1:16:39.194
Danny!

1:16:48.370 --> 1:16:49.971
Why does he want
to see me?

1:16:50.104 --> 1:16:52.674
[Al] 'Cause he's the boss.
He says he wants to meet you.

1:17:06.220 --> 1:17:07.656
[car door opens]

1:17:09.190 --> 1:17:10.359
Hop in.

1:17:21.302 --> 1:17:25.641
Frank and Glen have told me
great things about you, Daniel.

1:17:26.107 --> 1:17:27.341
Really?

1:17:28.075 --> 1:17:30.678
The way we see it,
this works out,

1:17:31.212 --> 1:17:33.215
could become
a regular deal.

1:17:34.982 --> 1:17:38.086
See, we're looking to expand
our operations in Thailand.

1:17:38.553 --> 1:17:40.255
We'd like you
to help us out.

1:17:41.056 --> 1:17:44.859
Well, Don, I'd--
I'd really like to help you...

1:17:45.760 --> 1:17:47.329
but I-I can't afford
to go to Thailand.

1:17:47.462 --> 1:17:48.730
Hmm?

1:17:49.331 --> 1:17:51.866
Well, how'd you get
the money for the train ticket?

1:17:52.534 --> 1:17:54.703
I spent everything
I had on it.

1:17:55.470 --> 1:17:57.939
[Don] Well, you know...

1:17:58.773 --> 1:18:00.108
from now on,

1:18:00.242 --> 1:18:02.209
I'm taking care
of everything.

1:18:02.343 --> 1:18:06.481
Flight, hotel, expenses,
the whole shebang.

1:18:06.614 --> 1:18:09.551
No more fucking around, kid.
You're going to Thailand.

1:18:09.684 --> 1:18:11.519
Well, what about
my passport?

1:18:12.120 --> 1:18:13.921
Don't worry.
Al took care of it.

1:18:14.055 --> 1:18:16.223
We fast-tracked it.
Ready to be picked up.

1:18:16.691 --> 1:18:20.195
Yeah, we even got you a hotel
room right next to the airport.

1:18:20.328 --> 1:18:22.564
You're going
to Thailand tomorrow.

1:18:22.697 --> 1:18:24.899
Tomorrow? Daniel.

1:18:25.033 --> 1:18:28.236
It's just a couple of days.
Quick in and out.

1:18:29.904 --> 1:18:32.174
Thanks, Daniel. Yeah.

1:18:39.414 --> 1:18:40.449
All right,
let's go.

1:18:43.518 --> 1:18:44.986
Come on.

1:18:56.965 --> 1:19:00.501
[George H.W. Bush on monitor]
And I challenge the Democrats
to stand up on this point.

1:19:01.169 --> 1:19:02.704
They say this is a war.

1:19:02.837 --> 1:19:04.406
Then treat it as such.

1:19:04.539 --> 1:19:08.744
We've got to fight the drug war
on all four fronts at once.

1:19:08.877 --> 1:19:12.079
Shrinking the supply
by destroying crops and labs

1:19:12.213 --> 1:19:14.482
and by patrolling
our borders vigorously,

1:19:14.616 --> 1:19:18.420
increasing both the certainty
and the severity of punishment--

1:19:25.259 --> 1:19:28.929
If you sell drugs,
you will be caught.
And when you're caught--

1:19:29.063 --> 1:19:30.498
Norm. [turns off monitor]

1:19:31.065 --> 1:19:33.134
This stuff is gold.
Did you know that the DEA

1:19:33.267 --> 1:19:35.203
might have been pressuring
the BC police to get results?

1:19:35.336 --> 1:19:37.739
I mean, if we can find out
what the US quota system is--

1:19:37.872 --> 1:19:39.941
Victor, listen. What?

1:19:40.075 --> 1:19:41.809
I've been reassigned
to another project.

1:19:41.943 --> 1:19:43.478
That's just gonna
have to wait, man.

1:19:43.611 --> 1:19:45.213
Well, apparently,
it can't.

1:19:45.814 --> 1:19:47.415
Look, I-I love
this junkie story too,

1:19:47.549 --> 1:19:49.417
but Randy doesn't want me
to work on it, so...

1:19:49.550 --> 1:19:51.919
The Globe paid for half
of our investigation.

1:19:52.720 --> 1:19:54.789
It doesn't make any sense to
take our foot off the gas now.

1:19:54.922 --> 1:19:58.392
If we just go to BC,
we dig a little bit, we're-- [knocking on door]

1:19:58.993 --> 1:20:01.229
Victor, Randy
wants to see you.

1:20:05.934 --> 1:20:07.402
[sighs]

1:20:08.069 --> 1:20:09.571
[knocks on glass]

1:20:10.338 --> 1:20:11.372
Come in.

1:20:11.706 --> 1:20:13.108
Have a seat.

1:20:15.210 --> 1:20:18.313
Victor, I've got
to let you go.

1:20:21.082 --> 1:20:23.184
I thought you said
that the show

1:20:23.818 --> 1:20:25.920
was kicking ass
since I got here.

1:20:26.053 --> 1:20:28.522
Yeah. I don't have
a choice.

1:20:28.656 --> 1:20:29.957
It's budget cuts.

1:20:30.091 --> 1:20:31.960
You know I left
The Globe and Mail, right?

1:20:32.093 --> 1:20:34.829
Yeah, I know.

1:20:35.863 --> 1:20:39.467
This doesn't have anything
to do with the junkie
investigation, does it?

1:20:39.601 --> 1:20:41.035
No, no.

1:20:41.669 --> 1:20:45.606
Nothing at all to do
with the federal police
or anything like that?

1:20:46.340 --> 1:20:48.476
It's got nothing
to do with that.

1:20:51.679 --> 1:20:53.248
[sighs]

1:21:03.959 --> 1:21:06.527
[knocks on door] Yeah. Yeah,
it'll be fine.

1:21:06.661 --> 1:21:10.331
Yeah. No, no. It's not
a question of the space.

1:21:10.598 --> 1:21:11.733
Look at this.

1:21:11.866 --> 1:21:14.035
Yeah. No, no,
space is fine.

1:21:14.169 --> 1:21:16.504
That's not an issue.
It's the, uh...

1:21:16.971 --> 1:21:19.174
It's the, uh... Hang--
No, hang on a second.

1:21:21.075 --> 1:21:22.544
Victor, a call for you.

1:21:22.677 --> 1:21:24.312
One second, Bianca.

1:21:26.414 --> 1:21:29.117
So, uh,
what did he want?

1:21:29.951 --> 1:21:31.486
Uh...

1:21:32.487 --> 1:21:33.788
I got fired.

1:21:33.921 --> 1:21:36.625
What? Why?

1:21:38.159 --> 1:21:39.793
I'm not sure.

1:21:39.927 --> 1:21:41.429
[scoffs]

1:21:46.434 --> 1:21:48.169
Yeah? [man] Uh, Mr. Malarek.

1:21:48.302 --> 1:21:50.905
I'm calling from the
Public Complaints Commission.

1:21:51.039 --> 1:21:52.740
Complaints Commission?
I've never heard of you.

1:21:52.873 --> 1:21:54.942
Yeah, we're a new entity.
Listen.

1:21:55.076 --> 1:21:59.580
I just read your article
on the Daniel Léger case.
I'd like to discuss it with you.

1:21:59.714 --> 1:22:01.682
I don't work for
The Globe anymore.

1:22:01.816 --> 1:22:03.818
In fact, I don't work
for anyone. So I won't be
doing any follow-ups.

1:22:03.951 --> 1:22:07.288
No, I-I'm not calling to give
you information, Mr. Malarek.

1:22:07.421 --> 1:22:10.025
I think maybe I'd like
to make this our first case.

1:22:10.158 --> 1:22:13.094
I need the details
of your investigation.

1:22:27.908 --> 1:22:29.377
All right, stop.

1:22:30.645 --> 1:22:32.313
[knocking on door]

1:22:32.647 --> 1:22:33.682
[door opens]

1:22:35.015 --> 1:22:36.083
Oh, hey, buddy.

1:22:36.217 --> 1:22:37.986
How are you doing?

1:22:38.653 --> 1:22:39.587
Good.

1:22:39.721 --> 1:22:41.790
Come on in. Relax.

1:22:42.424 --> 1:22:46.127
Flight leaves tomorrow.
Frank will call you
with the exact time.

1:22:46.261 --> 1:22:47.929
And make sure
he's on the fucking plane.

1:22:48.062 --> 1:22:49.631
Don't worry.
He'll be there.

1:22:52.733 --> 1:22:55.170
Do you mind if we stay here
a couple more days?

1:22:55.903 --> 1:22:57.138
No, sure.

1:22:57.739 --> 1:22:58.773
What?

1:22:58.906 --> 1:23:00.642
I need to go to Montreal.

1:23:00.775 --> 1:23:02.576
Why? Uh...

1:23:02.710 --> 1:23:06.314
I need to speak to
the Complaints Commission
about the federal police.

1:23:07.181 --> 1:23:08.950
You're making a complaint
against the feds?

1:23:09.084 --> 1:23:11.519
No, the Complaints Commission
read my article in The Globe,

1:23:11.652 --> 1:23:14.655
and they want to talk to me
about the Daniel Léger case.

1:23:15.223 --> 1:23:17.124
Well, what have you got
to do with that?

1:23:17.258 --> 1:23:18.993
Well, I interviewed him,

1:23:19.127 --> 1:23:22.430
so they want me to testify
as a witness.

1:23:27.035 --> 1:23:29.671
I'm gonna go check
on the meat loaf.

1:23:38.246 --> 1:23:40.614
You lost both your jobs
because of this thing.

1:23:40.748 --> 1:23:43.151
Don't you think it's time
to just drop it?

1:23:43.284 --> 1:23:44.719
I'm not gonna drop it now.

1:23:44.852 --> 1:23:47.522
We just put our finger
on something-- No, you--

1:23:48.790 --> 1:23:50.425
I have never complained
about your work.

1:23:50.558 --> 1:23:52.193
Okay? I am proud
of what you do.

1:23:52.326 --> 1:23:53.561
I have always been proud.

1:23:53.694 --> 1:23:55.330
But you've got
to drop this thing.

1:23:55.463 --> 1:23:58.766
Well, this isn't my job.
This is a court investigation.

1:23:58.900 --> 1:24:01.236
These people
attacked us.

1:24:03.337 --> 1:24:05.540
To be fair,
we don't know who attacked us.

1:24:05.673 --> 1:24:08.142
They weren't trying to hurt you.
They were trying to scare me,
as usual.

1:24:08.276 --> 1:24:11.846
We can't let these guys
change the way
we live our lives just because--

1:24:11.980 --> 1:24:13.414
Oh, my God.

1:24:14.348 --> 1:24:17.318
What? It obviously doesn't
matter what I say.

1:24:17.618 --> 1:24:19.587
Of course it matters
what you say.

1:24:20.221 --> 1:24:22.623
It's just that Léger
is out there on his own.

1:24:22.756 --> 1:24:25.727
I mean, what am I
supposed to do?
Leave him out there to rot?

1:24:28.029 --> 1:24:29.363
Come on.

1:24:29.997 --> 1:24:32.166
You can't save everybody.

1:24:32.300 --> 1:24:33.568
You have a daughter now.

1:24:34.669 --> 1:24:36.971
What if it was
our daughter, hmm?

1:24:37.105 --> 1:24:38.773
Out there. It's not.

1:24:38.907 --> 1:24:41.642
Well, what if it was,
and she was dying
in a Thai prison,

1:24:41.776 --> 1:24:43.778
and the government
had abandoned her?

1:24:43.911 --> 1:24:45.580
Like you are?

1:24:47.915 --> 1:24:50.818
This whole thing isn't
about Léger or our daughter.

1:24:50.951 --> 1:24:52.286
It's about you.

1:24:52.420 --> 1:24:54.989
But this guy isn't you.
Okay?

1:24:55.123 --> 1:24:57.725
When Social Services took
you away, you were a kid.
You were innocent.

1:24:57.859 --> 1:24:59.326
This guy's a criminal,
for Christ's sake.

1:24:59.460 --> 1:25:01.529
The government
fucked him over.

1:25:02.764 --> 1:25:05.666
I know what it feels like
to have the shit kicked
out of you every day

1:25:06.267 --> 1:25:09.671
and to wonder if anybody
is ever gonna come
look out for you.

1:25:10.905 --> 1:25:12.373
No one ever does.

1:25:12.941 --> 1:25:15.276
I hope you guys are hungry.

1:25:15.943 --> 1:25:17.779
It's comfort food.

1:25:20.748 --> 1:25:22.316
Usually, it gets
a bigger ovation

1:25:22.449 --> 1:25:24.752
when I arrive
with a meat loaf. [laughs]

1:25:27.088 --> 1:25:30.891
[announcer]
Our first big point
in this semifinal match.

1:25:31.025 --> 1:25:32.827
[announcer continues
on TV]

1:25:33.995 --> 1:25:37.432
It becomes balletic.
That is McEnroe magic
at its best.

1:25:37.565 --> 1:25:39.134
[snoring]

1:25:41.268 --> 1:25:43.671
[tennis ball
hitting rackets]

1:25:45.440 --> 1:25:48.142
[crowd groans] And that's a tough spot to hit,

1:25:48.275 --> 1:25:50.310
trying to get it
into that corner,

1:25:50.444 --> 1:25:52.313
the forehand of his opponent.

1:26:13.134 --> 1:26:15.503
[Michael in French]

1:26:58.746 --> 1:27:00.648
[Don]
You're not gonna believe this.
I asked for Léger's mug shot

1:27:00.781 --> 1:27:02.650
for the cash request
on the drug transaction.

1:27:02.784 --> 1:27:05.520
Yeah. C Division sent me this.

1:27:07.621 --> 1:27:09.157
What the hell is that?

1:27:09.290 --> 1:27:10.825
Robert Léger.

1:27:11.226 --> 1:27:13.093
We've been working
off the wrong record.

1:27:13.227 --> 1:27:14.629
No, I don't know.

1:27:14.762 --> 1:27:16.931
Our guy changes
his first name all the time.

1:27:17.064 --> 1:27:18.232
I've seen a long list.

1:27:18.632 --> 1:27:20.968
Besides,
the birth date's a match.

1:27:21.102 --> 1:27:22.803
Right. The name matches.

1:27:22.937 --> 1:27:24.872
The date and location
of birth matches.

1:27:25.005 --> 1:27:26.407
The mug shot doesn't.

1:27:26.540 --> 1:27:29.110
Well, C Division
sent the wrong photo.

1:27:29.510 --> 1:27:30.845
No, that's unlikely.

1:27:31.945 --> 1:27:33.481
I'll take care of it.

1:27:36.750 --> 1:27:39.153
[Cooper]
So, what's the story on this?

1:27:39.286 --> 1:27:44.258
Well, Daniel Léger exists in
the Social gSecurity data bank.

1:27:44.392 --> 1:27:46.894
Mm-hmm. He's got
a driver's license.

1:27:47.027 --> 1:27:49.930
He's from Quebec,
but he's got no criminal record.

1:27:50.063 --> 1:27:52.233
Hmm. And Robert Léger?

1:27:52.834 --> 1:27:55.836
[man] Robert Léger
and Daniel Léger are
two different people.

1:27:55.970 --> 1:28:00.441
And, uh, Robert Léger
is the fellow with
the criminal record.

1:28:00.574 --> 1:28:02.677
[Cooper] Okay. Thanks.

1:28:14.521 --> 1:28:17.325
Excuse me.
Do you know a Mr. Porn?

1:28:18.092 --> 1:28:19.727
Tuk-tuk driver,
Mr. Porn?

1:28:19.860 --> 1:28:22.029
[speaking Thai]

1:28:22.162 --> 1:28:23.865
Over there? Thanks.

1:28:41.315 --> 1:28:43.084
Are you,
uh, Mr. Porn?

1:28:46.187 --> 1:28:47.755
Go sit with Al
for a bit.

1:28:47.889 --> 1:28:49.324
Yeah.

1:28:59.200 --> 1:29:00.668
Can't sleep?

1:29:02.503 --> 1:29:04.672
I just hope
we didn't forget anything.

1:29:04.805 --> 1:29:07.408
Did you get all
the transaction cash we wanted?

1:29:07.541 --> 1:29:09.410
